
# Resume Builder Windsurf Rules (Compact)

## Core
- Rails 8, server-rendered, HTML-first
- Clean, small, readable, production-ready
- Prefer clarity, stability, simplicity

## Structure
- Controllers: HTTP only
- Models: domain logic
- Services: workflows
- Components: UI reuse
- Jobs: async
- Single responsibility

## Rails
- Follow conventions & repo style
- Yarn + jsbundling-rails
- Strong params, validations, transactions
- Prefer AR over raw SQL
- Avoid N+1, unnecessary work
- Consistent JSON (string keys)

## App Direction
- HTML-first, JSON only when needed
- Shared preview/PDF rendering
- Follow auth + background patterns
- Consistent APIs (status + structure)

## Errors & Logs
- No silent failures
- Log useful context
- Clean user-safe errors
- No debug leftovers

## Docs & Tests
- Comment only non-obvious logic
- Keep docs/tests updated
- Test behavior, not internals
- Mock-friendly design

## Maintenance
- Fix nearby issues when safe
- Allow small improvements
- Track risks/follow-ups
- Self-review before done
- Remove unused code

## Commits
- Small, focused commits
- Clear messages
- Verify tests/lint/migrations/docs
- No dead code/clutter
- Never commit dependencies
- Push per logical change

## Security
- No hardcoded secrets
- Use Rails config + DB
- Validate/sanitize input
- Move heavy work async
- Prefer idempotency
- Flag risks + rollback

## Windsurf
- Use vikinger-ui-agent when needed
- Themes = inspiration only

## Output
- Match project style
- Production-ready only
- Include auth/errors/tests/docs if needed
- Add TODOs/placeholders
- Flag external issues + suggestions